who don't have fan clubs.

232
00:11:30,233 --> 00:11:34,433
My chest...

233
00:11:34,433 --> 00:11:36,333
Guys, guys, guys.

234
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:38,267
Are those numbers
supposed to spike like that?

235
00:11:38,267 --> 00:11:39,833
[EKG BEEPING RAPIDLY]

236
00:11:39,833 --> 00:11:40,833
Ah, so we're all pretending

237
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:43,000
- I'm invisible now?
- Did you enjoy lunch?

238
00:11:43,033 --> 00:11:45,100
Don't blame me if you're lonely.
You work too much!

239
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:49,033
- Yeah, when's the next one?
- Don't act nice, Grim!

240
00:11:49,033 --> 00:11:51,200
Grim. Your parents
really committed to that.

241
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:53,233
Yeah, but let's not talk
about me.

242
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:55,367
Are you dating anyone?
Are you curious?

243
00:11:55,367 --> 00:11:58,300
How would you like it
if I never move on, huh?!

244
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,700
There was one guy.

245
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:02,433
But Ros says that he shops
in the same aisle.

246
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:05,100
Hm.

247
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:09,933
[ROS GASPS]

248
00:12:09,933 --> 00:12:11,267
They're right!

249
00:12:11,267 --> 00:12:13,400
Grim gave your flowers
and cake to Noa.

250
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,367
[COVER THUDS]

251
00:12:20,433 --> 00:12:21,800
And now I'm hungry.

252
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:25,433
[PHONE BUZZING]

253
00:12:25,433 --> 00:12:28,167
- [PHONE BUZZING]
- [GEORGE SIGHS]

254
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:31,400
Dude, I'm going to punch
someone, I swear to God!

255
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:36,767
[QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:39,200
Are you picking on me because
you grew up without a father,

257
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:42,233
or because I didn't allow you
to date until you're 21?

258
00:12:42,233 --> 00:12:44,900
- I'm not!
- Stranger danger!

259
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:48,067
Don't punch him yet.

260
00:12:48,933 --> 00:12:50,433
I need my camera.

261
00:12:50,433 --> 00:12:55,867
[PHONE BUZZING]

262
00:12:55,867 --> 00:12:58,467
[GRIM] So, did you enjoy
our time together?

263
00:12:58,467 --> 00:13:01,000
No, the guy should pay
for lunch!

264
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:01,967
[PHONE BUZZES]

265
00:13:02,967 --> 00:13:05,767
- Yeah, sure.
- Yeah.

266
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:06,733
Grim!

267
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,800
I taught him that.

268
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:18,000
Who told you
that you could give

269
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:20,200
my Red Ribbon cake
and flowers to Noa?

270
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,800
Huh? What-- What flowers?

271
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:24,433
I told you, it's not from him!
He's a--

272
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,300
- [ROS] Punch him already!
- Yeah, do it.

273
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:32,333
Wait, you bought those flowers
for me?

274
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,567
[ROS] No,
it's for his boyfriend!

275
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:35,800
George!

276
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:39,833
Babe!

277
00:13:41,967 --> 00:13:46,033
He's... a she?

278
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:47,867
(In Tagalog)
Didn't see that coming either.

279
00:13:47,867 --> 00:13:48,833
[INTERCOM CHIMING]

280
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,433
[DONDON ON SPEAKER]<i> Um...
</i> Is this on?

281
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:51,967
<i>Camille,
is this the right button?</i>

282
00:13:51,967 --> 00:13:54,400
<i>Paging Nurse Noa!
Code, um...</i>

283
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,800
Yeah, I'm not totally
sure what to say, but like...

284
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:58,867
Come to Room 5-0...
Wait, Camille,

285
00:13:58,867 --> 00:14:00,200
<i> is it 5-0...</i>

286
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:03,067
<i>Yeah, it's 5-0-0.
Okay, thanks, bye!</i>

287
00:14:03,067 --> 00:14:04,400
[RECEIVER CLICKS]

288
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,900
That's it.

289
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:08,467
I'm really starting
to hate Valentine's Day.

290
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:11,067
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

291
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:14,933
- [MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY]
- [NOA SIGHS SHARPLY]

292
00:14:14,933 --> 00:14:16,567
- What is it?
- Is that normal?

293
00:14:16,567 --> 00:14:18,033
Of course it's not.

294
00:14:18,033 --> 00:14:19,867
Why hasn't anyone
paged the attending?

295
00:14:19,867 --> 00:14:21,533
She has a heartbreak.

296
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:23,367
[SIGHS] Heartbreak?

297
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:27,333
You want to hear
about heartbreak, Camille?

298
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:29,233
I just spent the entire day

299
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:32,333
thinking someone
actually sent me flowers.

300
00:14:32,333 --> 00:14:34,233
I mean, who does that?

301
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:35,567
Me!

302
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:36,633
I live here.

303
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:38,000
I chart here.

304
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,867
I nap by the vending machine.

305
00:14:40,867 --> 00:14:44,067
My crush, who I thought was gay,
actually has a girlfriend.

306
00:14:44,067 --> 00:14:47,200
And the guy who
supposedly sent me flowers?

307
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:50,000
Total fraud! Of course.

308
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,200
(In Tagalog) See? I told you so!

309
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,367
(In English) That's it!

310
00:14:53,367 --> 00:14:55,900
I hate Valentine's Day.

311
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:57,933
Cupid can choke.

312
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,600
Well, if he's a real angel,
I'm sorry.

313
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,967
[SNICKERS, LAUGHS]

314
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,367
[GASPS]

315
00:15:04,367 --> 00:15:05,433
Oh my god!

316
00:15:05,433 --> 00:15:08,300
I am so sorry.
I thought you were unconscious.

317
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,000
You're right.

318
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,133
(In Spanish) It sucks.

319
00:15:11,133 --> 00:15:13,167
[LAUGHING]

320
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:16,067
(In English) Hi, I'm Noa.

321
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:19,200
(In Spanish) Hello, I'm Amore.

322
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,500
(In English) Nice to meet you.

323
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,367
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

324
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:24,500
Hey, look!
Her levels are improving.

325
00:15:24,500 --> 00:15:26,200
[MACHINE BEEPING STEADILY]

326
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,033
- [CHUCKLES]
- Wonderful!

327
00:15:28,033 --> 00:15:28,900
[CAMILLE SCOFFS]

328
00:15:28,900 --> 00:15:31,033
Imagine how many
lives would be saved

329
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:33,500
if HIPAA allows me
to post about this.

330
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,033
[CHUCKLES]

331
00:15:35,067 --> 00:15:36,667
Look, we're not
out of the woods yet,

332
00:15:36,667 --> 00:15:38,433
but that laugh
bought us some time.

333
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,367
(In Spanish)
You're very funny.

334
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:43,533
[CHUCKLES, SNORTS]

335
00:15:44,967 --> 00:15:46,233
(In English) It's okay.

336
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:48,967
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

337
00:15:48,967 --> 00:15:50,967
[INHALES, EXHALES HEAVILY]

338
00:15:57,700 --> 00:16:00,033
- Hey.
- What happened? I kept calling.

339
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:02,533
I know, sorry.
Work just got really crazy.

340
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:04,467
I-I got you some stuff.

341
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:06,500
Thank you.

342
00:16:08,633 --> 00:16:09,667
[GEORGE SIGHS IN RELIEF]

343
00:16:09,667 --> 00:16:12,167
[COMICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:16:12,167 --> 00:16:13,133
Psst!

345
00:16:15,533 --> 00:16:16,700
Um...

346
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:19,333
Give me just one minute.
I'll meet you at the benches.

347
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,200
Okay.

348
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:25,733
[COMICAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:27,033
- What?
- Here.

350
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:32,167
Is this an apology?

351
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:34,733
My Valentine's gift.

352
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:38,033
And I realized...

353
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:40,367
I was the gossip and the liar.

354
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:44,067
That wasn't just a running gag?

355
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:46,000
Um, yeah, sure.

356
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,067
Let's go with that.

357
00:16:49,267 --> 00:16:50,567
It's okay.

358
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:52,300
I know you'd love me
no matter what.

359
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,267
[ROS CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

360
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:56,033
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

361
00:16:56,033 --> 00:16:57,367
Happy Valentine's, dude.

362
00:16:58,700 --> 00:17:03,000
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

363
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,000
[WHISTLES]

364
00:17:04,767 --> 00:17:06,267
[GEORGE CHUCKLES]

365
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:16,167
[GRIM]
You wanted to see me?

366
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:20,100
- Please, have a seat.
- [TESS SCOFFS]

367
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:21,500
(In Tagalog)
You're in trouble.

368
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:23,533
(In English)
You can stop pretending

369
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:24,633
you don't see her now.

370
00:17:29,067 --> 00:17:30,233
[GRIM CHUCKLES]

371
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,567
[EXHALES]

372
00:17:33,567 --> 00:17:35,567
I think I'll sit over here.

373
00:17:38,233 --> 00:17:39,800
[GRUNTS]

374
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:42,133
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

375
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,767
What gave it away?

376
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:45,533
How much time do we have?

377
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,467
I don't know.
Not long.

378
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:50,767
Right, Tess?

379
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:54,200
(In Tagalog) I will be here
as long my daughter needs me.

380
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,100
(In English) Yeah,
but you feel it, don't you?

381
00:17:57,267 --> 00:18:01,467
Your tether to this world
is loosening.

382
00:18:02,700 --> 00:18:05,167
You think ghosts can just
wander around in purgatory

383
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:06,667
for the rest of time?

384
00:18:07,467 --> 00:18:09,200
Hmm?

385
00:18:09,200 --> 00:18:11,400
- He's lying.
- No, I'm not.

386
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,433
[HUFFS]

387
00:18:12,433 --> 00:18:14,600
You have your chain of command.
I have mine.

388
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:19,733
Bureaucracy exists everywhere,
living or dead.

389
00:18:19,733 --> 00:18:22,567
Someone's always going to
get chewed up, right?

390
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:24,400
The mystery is...

391
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:26,467
who gets bit first.

392
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:28,267
(In Tagalog)
Wow, you're good.

393
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:31,500
You're like The Riddler.
So mysterious.

394
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:33,800
Where's Batman?

395
00:18:33,800 --> 00:18:35,667
(In English)
So, am I being fired?

396
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:38,533
I was really starting
to enjoy the food here.

397
00:18:38,533 --> 00:18:39,500
No.

398
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:43,367
Look, I've seen you help people.

399
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,200
You don't have to take them,
you can save them.

400
00:18:49,233 --> 00:18:51,433
Well, since I'm not being fired,

401
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:53,233
I have to get back to work.

402
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:55,133
I didn't say you can go.

403
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:56,767
Well, I'm on the clock, so...

404
00:18:59,467 --> 00:19:01,267
We both know how this works.

405
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:06,633
Every rule shattered
demands its due.

406
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:09,467
That's how it works.
That's the truth.

407
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:10,767
Then I'll pay it.

408
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:13,500
Now you can go.

409
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:20,233
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

410
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:21,700
I have the sudden urge to do

411
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:25,367
a 30 French Foley,
front full insertion.

412
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:29,833
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

413
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:39,267
What was that about?

414
00:19:39,267 --> 00:19:40,267
Nothing.

415
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:42,867
Happy Valentine's Day, babe.

416
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:44,567
Happy Valentine's, babe.

417
00:19:49,733 --> 00:19:50,700
George!

418
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:51,867
Yes, babe?

419
00:19:51,867 --> 00:19:52,833
Who's Noa?

420
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:59,767
[COMICAL MUSIC PLAYING]
